  "text": "Interpretation of these types of studies is complicated by the fact that RNA viruses in infected hosts, including MERS-CoV-infected dromedary camels, consist of swarms of closely related RNA molecules (quasispecies). [CITATION_1] On transmission to a new host, only one or a few members of the RNA virus swarm are transmitted, which makes it diffi cult to isolate the exact same virus from both donors and recipients.",
